In a small #pot, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Drain @corn{1} and pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%drizzle} in a large pan over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover pan if corn begins to pop!

Turn off heat; transfer corn to a #small bowl. Stir in @fresh red salsa{4%oz}; set aside until ready to serve.

Open package of @tofu{1} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%large drizzle} in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Add chicken, green pepper, onion, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are just beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken and veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Add @water{1/4%cup} and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is cooked through and sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a second #small bowl. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls and top with chicken and veggies. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and corn salsa. Drizzle crema over everything and serve.